k, England, United Kingdom","Mondeford Manor, Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, England","Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barrett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): probably a nickname for a quarrelsome person, from Old French <i>barat</i>, Middle English <i>bar(r)at</i>, <i>bar(r)et(te)</i> ‘trouble, distress’, later ‘deception, fraud; contention, strife’. Through Norman settlement it also became common in Ireland, where it was Gaelicized as <b>Baróid</b> (Munster) and <b>Baréid</b> (Connacht)."],"variants":[{"name":"Barret","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Matthieu, Mirlande, Philippe.","English: variant of   Barrett  .","French: derivative of the topographic name   Barre   1 ‘barrier’, or a habitational name from a place called with this word. This surname (in any of the two possible senses; see also 3 below) is also found in Haiti."]},{"name":"Berrett","meanings":["English (Wiltshire): variant of   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Baratta","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Carmine, Pasquale, Alfonse, Antonio, Carmela, Guido, Salvatore, Vincenzo.","Italian: occupational name for a market trader, especially in northern Italy, from <i>baratta</i> ‘exchange, sale, buying and selling’, a derivative of <i>barattare</i> ‘to barter’. See also   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Barritt","meanings":["English: variant of   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Barratt","meanings":["English: variant of   Barrett  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Barrett was born in 1385, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She married Osbert Mundeford IV in 1400, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 6 sons and 1 daughter. She died on 3 August 1456, in her hometown, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1385–3 August 1456":"1385–3. august 1456","1381–1456":"1381–1456","1401–1460":"1401–1460","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1410–1465":"1410–1465","1415–1483":"1415–1483","1425–1467":"1425–1467","1441–1467":"1441–1467","–1460":"–1460","1385–1456":"1385–1456","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","1460":"1460","1381":"1381","3 August 1456":"3. august 1456","1415":"1415","1425":"1425","1401":"1401","1467":"1467","1456":"1456","1400":"1400","about 1405":"umbes 1405","1410":"1410","1465":"1465","1441":"1441","1463":"1463","1405":"1405","Feltwell, Norfolk, England":"Feltwell, Norfolk, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mondeford Manor, Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, England","Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1385–3 August 1456":"1385–3. elokuuta 1456","1381–1456":"1381–1456","1401–1460":"1401–1460","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1410–1465":"1410–1465","1415–1483":"1415–1483","1425–1467":"1425–1467","1441–1467":"1441–1467","–1460":"–1460","1385–1456":"1385–1456","1385":"1385","1483":"1483","1460":"1460","1381":"1381","3 August 1456":"3. elokuuta 1456","1415":"1415","1425":"1425","1401":"1401","1467":"1467","1456":"1456","1400":"1400","about 1405":"noin 1405","1410":"1410","1465":"1465","1441":"1441","1463":"1463","1405":"1405","Feltwell, Norfolk, England":"Feltwell, Norfolk, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Mondeford Manor, Hockwold, Norfolk, E